<H2><U>
Native American Legends About Beavers
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.lib.unb.ca/Texts/QWERTY/Qweb/qwerte/mic_mal/sugtxten.htm
">Glooscap and the Beavers</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://website.nbm-mnb.ca/Koluskap/English/Stories/story2.php
">Koluskap and the Giant Beaver</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://pyramidmesa.netfirms.com/passam1.html
">Glooscap Shrinks the Animals</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Wabanaki Indian legends about the culture hero Glooskap fighting beaver monsters and making them smaller.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.uwosh.edu/coehs/cmagproject/ethnomath/legend/legend12.htm
">How the Beaver Got His Tail</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Ojibwe legend about Beaver's flat tail.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.mpm.edu/wirp/ICW-138.html#beaver
">Beaver and Muskrat</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Menominee legend about Beaver stealing Muskrat's tail.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><B><A HREF="
http://www.indianlegend.com/lenape/lenape_001.htm
">The Good Looking Woman</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <B><A HREF="
http://www.nativeamericanembassy.net/www.lenni-lenape.com/www/html/LenapeArchives/LenapeSet-01/prtymaid.html
">The Pretty Maiden</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Lenape legends about a girl punished for being rude to Beaver.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.native-languages.org/creestory4.htm
">Cree Flood Myth</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Cree legend about a giant beaver that caused the earth to flood.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><B><A HREF="
http://www.pyramidmesa.com/blackfoot2.htm
">The Sacred Weed</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*">  <b><A HREF="
http://www.bigorrin.org/archive76.htm
">A Tobacco Legend</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Blackfoot legends about the beavers teaching people to grow tobacco.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.firstpeople.us/FP-Html-Legends/BeaverMedicine-Blackfoot.html
">Beaver Medicine</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://www.firstpeople.us/FP-Html-Legends/TheStoryofTwoBrothers-Blackfoot.html
">The Story of Two Brothers</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Blackfoot stories about a Great Beaver that saved an unjustly accused man and sent beaver medicine to the people.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><B><A HREF="
http://www.firstpeople.us/FP-Html-Legends/BeaverMeat-Blackfoot.html
">Beaver Meat</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Blackfoot legend warning against killing beavers.
<BR>

<H2><U>
Recommended Books of Beaver Stories from Native American Myth and Legend
</u><BR><font size=2>Our organization earns a commission from any book bought through these links</font>
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0803216408/natilangofthe-20
">Beaver Steals Fire</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A Native American legend about Beaver and the origin of fire, presented by the Salish and Kootenai tribes.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0803728522/natilangofthe-20
">Turtle's Race With Beaver</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Lively picture book illustrating a Seneca Indian legend about Beaver.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0452276500/natilangofthe-20
">Spirits of the Earth: A Guide to Native American Nature Symbols, Stories, and Ceremonies</A></B>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Book by a Karuk elder about the meanings of Indian animal spirits, including a chapter on beavers.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1555911277/natilangofthe-20
">Native American Animal Stories</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Good collection of American Indian tales about beavers and other animals, told by Abenaki storyteller Joseph Bruchac. 
<BR>




